                        <interp inst="t18730818-name-632" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CROOME</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a detective-serjeant of Scotlaud Yard—I was first instructed in April—I accompanied Mr. Field on his first visit to King's, and from there we went to Jewell's, where I heard a conversation between Mr. Field and Jewell—after leaving Jewell's we went to Castle's and had some conversation with George Castle—Mr. Field gave him the opportunity to find out the person he spoke of, and he promised to come and see Mr. Field on the 15th April—I never saw him again till I took him in custody at Paddington on 3rd June—I told him in the passage that I had been</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="187308180200"></xptr>
               <p>walk from my place—before Mrs. Castle was taken, in consequence of some<lb></lb>thing that was said to me, I went to Cookson's house; my mother and my husband went with me—when I got there I saw Mrs. Castle and her daughter—she said "Oh, <hi rend="italic">Liz I</hi> you have done for me, nobody has been taken till to-night; Rumble has <hi rend="italic">rounded</hi>"—I said I had seen the wax there, and told her what I had said to Mr. Field—she said "Oh, <hi rend="italic">Liz</hi> I you have done for me and my boy; all you have said to-night you can deny in the morning; take care what you say for my son George and me"—Sergeaut Croome then came in and took her in custody.</p>
