                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CROOME</hi>. I worked some time for Mrs. Castle; some<lb></lb>times in the yard and sometimes in the house—I took particular notice of Mrs. Scott, because people in the neighbourhood used to talk about her taking bundles out—I did not take notice of any other customer, because no other customer used to Come into the parlour—I used to do the house cleaning, and when she came I was always in the parlour—I was there from 8 in the morning till 7 at night—I saw her there on the Monday or Tuesday in the week I left, but not in the latter part of the week—I was first asked about this the end of April, after I left—I had not talked it over in—the meanwhile, and my attention had not been drawn to it—I don't know that Mrs. Scott brought a number of bags for Mrs. Castle in the bundle, as she finished them.</p>
